cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper focuses on deep learning-based visual sensing and its vulnerability to adversarial example attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a strategy of moving target defense (MTD) to generate multiple new deep models, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on an embedded computing board, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
